Topic 1 : Eighth Annual SRC / ARPA CIM-IC Workshop Call for Papers
Date : Mon , 21 Jun 93 15 : 28 : 38 EDT From : Andrzej Strojwas To : tcad-submit @ tcad . ee . ufl . edu Subject : CIM / IC Workshop
This is a reminder that the deadline for submitting abstracts to this year 's CIM IC is coming very soon . Below is a copy of the Call For Papers . Sorry if you got it several times by now .
Andrzej Strojwas
Eighth Annual SRC / ARPA CIM-IC Workshop August 24 through 26 , 1993 Call for Abstracts by June 25 , 1993
The eighth annual Workshop on Computer- Integrated Manufacturing for Integrated Circuits ( CIM-IC ) will be held August 24 through 26 , 1993 , at Carnegie Mellon University . This event is co- sponsored by the SRC and ARPA ( formerly known as DARPA ) . The broad objective is to stimulate interactions among industry , university , and government-agency workers , and to provide planning inputs for SRC Manufacturing Systems research .
In addition to working group discussions , the workshop agenda will include invited and contributed papers in the following areas and related topics :
- CIM System Integration - Industry CIM Needs - Coupling Manufacturing and Design - TCAD Tools - Process Specification - Process / Equipment Modeling , Monitoring , Control , and Diagnosis - Sensors , Monitors , and Test Structures - Statistical Techniques - Factory Modeling - Data Collection , Communication , Storage , Analysis , and Reporting - Scheduling - Tools for Business Decision Making
Abstracts are solicited from university researchers and are particularly encouraged from SRC member companies and from the equipment supplier community . Authors of accepted abstracts will be notified by July 9 . Accepted abstracts will be included in a workshop proceedings to be distributed after the meeting . Written papers will not be required .
Abstracts ( 300 - 500 words ) of proposed papers should be sent to the following address by June 25 :
Professor A . J . Strojwas Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering 2106 Hammerschlag Hall Carnegie Mellon University 5000 Forbes Avenue , Pittsburgh , PA 15213 FAX : 412 - 268 - 3204 E- mail : strojwas @ ece . cmu . edu
